Żubroń.label: Żubroń
Żubroń.description: Żubroń is a hybrid of domestic cattle and wisent. The wisent is the European bison; hence, the żubroń is analogous to the American beefalo. Wikipedia

Açaí palm.label: Açaí palm
Açaí palm.description: The açaí palm is a species of palm tree in the genus Euterpe cultivated for its fruit and superior hearts of palm. Its name comes from the Portuguese adaptation of the Tupian word ïwaca'i, '[fruit that] cries or expels water'. Wikipedia

Abies nebrodensis.label: Abies nebrodensis
Abies nebrodensis.description: Sicilian Fir is a fir native to the Nebrodi and Madonie mountains in northern Sicily. It is a medium-size evergreen coniferous tree growing to 15–25 m tall and with a trunk diameter of up to 1 m. It occurs at altitudes of 1400-1,600 m. Wikipedia

Abies nordmanniana.label: Abies nordmanniana
Abies nordmanniana.description: Abies nordmanniana, the Nordmann Fir, is a fir native to the mountains west and east of the Black Sea, in Turkey, Georgia, Russian Caucasus and northern parts of Armenia. Wikipedia

Abbott's Booby.label: Abbott's Booby
Abbott's Booby.description: Abbott’s Booby is an endangered seabird of the sulid family, which includes gannets and boobies. It is the largest bird of the family, and is placed within its own monotypic genus. Wikipedia

Abyssinian Roller.label: Abyssinian Roller
Abyssinian Roller.description: The Abyssinian Roller is a member of the roller family of birds which breeds across tropical Africa in a belt south of the Sahara, known as the Sahel. Wikipedia

Abraxas grossulariata.label: Abraxas grossulariata
Abraxas grossulariata.description: Abraxas grossulariata is a moth of the family Geometridae, native to the Palaearctic ecozone and North America. Its distinctive speckled colouration has given it a common name of Magpie Moth. Wikipedia

Acacia karroo.label: Vachellia karroo
Acacia karroo.description:
Vachellia karroo also known as the Sweet Thorn, is a species of Vachellia, native to southern Africa from southern Angola east to Mozambique, and south to South Africa.
It is a shrub or small to medium-sized tree which grows to height of 12m. Wikipedia

Acacia mellifera.label: Senegalia mellifera
Acacia mellifera.description: Senegalia mellifera is a common thorn tree in Africa. The name mellifera refers to its sweet-smelling blossoms and honey. Its lumber turns pitch black when oiled. Common names of the tree include Blackthorn and Swarthaak. Wikipedia

Acantharea.label: Acantharea
Acantharea.description: The Acantharea are a group of radiolarian protozoa, distinguished mainly by their skeletons. Wikipedia

Acanthicus.label: Acanthicus
Acanthicus.description:
Acanthicus is a genus of suckermouth armored catfishes native to South America.
The name Acanthicus is derived from the Greek, akanthikos meaning thorny, spiny. Fish of this genus are known as Lyre tail plecos. Wikipedia

Acanthobrahmaea europaea.label: Acanthobrahmaea europaea
Acanthobrahmaea europaea.description: The European Owl Moth is a lepidopteran from the family Brahmaeidae, the Brahmin moths. Wikipedia

Acanthurus.label: Acanthurus
Acanthurus.description: Acanthurus is the type genus of the family Acanthuridae. Approximately half of all members of the family are members of the genus Acanthurus. Wikipedia

Acanthurus achilles.label: Acanthurus achilles
Acanthurus achilles.description: Acanthurus achilles is a tropical fish with the common names Achilles Tang and Achilles surgeonfish. It is also a salt water habitat. Wikipedia

Acanthurus albipectoralis.label: Acanthurus albipectoralis
Acanthurus albipectoralis.description: The Whitefin surgeonfish is a marine reef tang in the fish family Acanthuridae. Individuals grow to a maximum length of 33 cm. Wikipedia

Acanthurus auranticavus.label: Acanthurus auranticavus
Acanthurus auranticavus.description: Acanthurus auranticavus, is a tropical fish with the common names Orange-socket surgeonfish and Ring-tail surgeon. It was named by Randall in 1956. Wikipedia

Acanthurus coeruleus.label: Acanthurus coeruleus
Acanthurus coeruleus.description: Acanthurus coeruleus is a surgeonfish found commonly in the Atlantic Ocean. It can grow up to 16 inches long. Wikipedia

Acanthurus guttatus.label: Acanthurus guttatus
Acanthurus guttatus.description: The Whitespotted surgeonfish or is a marine reef tang in the fish family Acanthuridae. It is found in shallow waters on reefs in the Indo-Pacific. Wikipedia

Acanthurus dussumieri.label: Acanthurus dussumieri
Acanthurus dussumieri.description: Acanthurus dussumieri is a Tang from the Indo-Pacific. It occasionally makes its way into the aquarium trade. It grows to a size of 54 cm in length. Wikipedia

Acanthurus maculiceps.label: Acanthurus maculiceps
Acanthurus maculiceps.description: Acanthurus maculiceps is a Tang from the Indo-West Pacific. It is known commonly as the white-freckled surgeonfish It occasionally makes its way into the aquarium trade. It grows to a size of 40 cm in length. Wikipedia

Acanthurus lineatus.label: Acanthurus lineatus
Acanthurus lineatus.description: Acanthurus lineatus, the lined surgeonfish, is a member of the family Acanthuridae, the surgeonfishes. Other common names include blue banded surgeonfish, blue-lined surgeonfish, clown surgeonfish, striped surgeonfish, and zebra surgeonfish. Wikipedia

Acanthurus japonicus.label: Acanthurus japonicus
Acanthurus japonicus.description: Acanthurus japonicus is a Tang from the Indo-West Pacific. It occasionally makes its way into the aquarium trade. It grows to a size of 21 cm in length. It is also known as Japan Surgeonfish, White-faced Surgeonfish and White-nose Surgeonfish. Wikipedia

Acanthurus monroviae.label: Acanthurus monroviae
Acanthurus monroviae.description: Acanthurus monroviae is a tropical fish which is found in the eastern Atlantic ocean. It is commercial in fisheries, and is also used in aquariums. It was first named by Franz Steindachner in 1876, and is known commonly as the Monrovia doctorfish. Wikipedia

Acanthurus nigricans.label: Whitecheek surgeonfish
Acanthurus nigricans.description: The whitecheek surgeonfish, also known as the goldenrim surgeonfish or yellow-spotted surgeonfish, Acanthurus nigricans, is a reef-associated tang found from the central Indo-Pacific area to the eastern Pacific coast, Hawaii included. Wikipedia

Acanthurus nigricauda.label: Acanthurus nigricauda
Acanthurus nigricauda.description: Acanthurus nigricauda is a tropical fish with the common name epaulette surgeonfish. Wikipedia

Acanthurus nigroris.label: Acanthurus nigroris
Acanthurus nigroris.description: Acanthurus nigroris is a Tang from the Indo-Pacific. It occasionally makes its way into the aquarium trade. It grows to a size of 25 cm in length. Wikipedia

Acanthurus olivaceus.label: Acanthurus olivaceus
Acanthurus olivaceus.description: Acanthurus olivaceus, also known as Orange band Surgeonfishor Orange-shoulder Surgeonfish, is a member of the family Acanthuridae, the surgeonfishes. It lives in tropical waters of the Indo-west Pacific. Wikipedia

Acanthurus polyzona.label: Acanthurus polyzona
Acanthurus polyzona.description: Acanthurus polyzona is a tropical fish found in coral reefs situated in the western Indian Ocean. It was first named by Pieter Bleeker in 1868, and is commonly known as the Black-barred surgeonfish or Zebra tang. Wikipedia

Acanthurus pyroferus.label: Acanthurus pyroferus
Acanthurus pyroferus.description: Acanthurus pyroferus is a species of fish in the family Acanthuridae, the unicornfishes and tangs. Its common names include chocolate surgeonfish, mimic surgeonfish, orange-gilled surgeonfish, Pacific mimic surgeon, and yellowspot surgeon. Wikipedia

Acanthurus randalli.label: Acanthurus randalli
Acanthurus randalli.description: Acanthurus randalli is a tropical fish found in the western Atlantic ocean. It was first named by Briggs and Caldwell in 1957, and is commonly known as the Gulf surgeonfish. Wikipedia

Acanthurus reversus.label: Acanthurus reversus
Acanthurus reversus.description: Acanthurus reversus is a tropical fish found in coral reefs in the Marquesas Islands. It was first named by Randall and Earle in 1999. Wikipedia

Acanthurus tennentii.label: Acanthurus tennentii
Acanthurus tennentii.description: The doubleband surgeonfish or lieutenant tang is a marine reef tang in the fish family Acanthuridae. The fish grows to a maximum length of 31 cm. Wikipedia

Acanthurus thompsoni.label: Acanthurus thompsoni
Acanthurus thompsoni.description: Acanthurus thompsoni is a tropical fish found in the Pacific and Indian Oceans. It is commonly known as the Thompson's surgeonfish. It is commercial in aquarium use. Wikipedia

Acanthurus triostegus.label: Acanthurus triostegus
Acanthurus triostegus.description: The manini is a small surgeonfish in family Acanthuridae of order Perciformes. It is about 5 inches long. It is whitish-yellow with zebra-like black stripes on its sides. It is also known as Convict Tang. Wikipedia

Acaste (genus).label: Acaste
Acaste (genus).description: Acaste is a genus of extinct trilobite of the order Phacopida which lived throughout the Silurian period. Wikipedia

Acer buergerianum.label: Acer buergerianum
Acer buergerianum.description: Acer buergerianum is a species of maple native to eastern China and Taiwan. Wikipedia

Acer carpinifolium.label: Acer carpinifolium
Acer carpinifolium.description: Acer carpinifolium is a species of maple native to Japan, on the islands of Honshū, Kyūshū, and Shikoku, where it grows in woodlands and alongside streams in mountainous areas. Wikipedia

Acer palmatum.label: Acer palmatum
Acer palmatum.description: Acer palmatum, called Japanese Maple or Smooth Japanese Maple is a species of woody plant native to Japan, North Korea, South Korea, China, eastern Mongolia, and southeast Russia. Wikipedia

Acer tegmentosum.label: Acer tegmentosum
Acer tegmentosum.description: Acer tegmentosum, Manchurian striped maple is a species of maple genus, which is natively found in the south of the Russian Far East, North-Eastern China and in Korea. Wikipedia

Acherontia atropos.label: Acherontia atropos
Acherontia atropos.description: Acherontia atropos is the most widely known of the three species of Death's-head Hawk moth. Acherontia species are notorious mainly for a vaguely skull-shaped pattern on the thorax. Wikipedia

Aciphylla.label: Aciphylla
Aciphylla.description: Aciphylla is a genus of about 40 species of plants in the Apiaceae family, endemic to New Zealand and Australia. They generally grow as tall spikes surrounded by rosettes of stiff, pointed leaves. Some species are known as Spaniard Grass. Wikipedia

Acristavus.label: Acristavus
Acristavus.description: Acristavus is a genus of saurolophine dinosaur. Fossils have been found from the Campanian Two Medicine Formation in Montana and Wahweap Formation in Utah. The type species A. gagslarsoni was named in 2011. Wikipedia

Aconitum lycoctonum.label: Aconitum lycoctonum
Aconitum lycoctonum.description:
Aconitum lycoctonum is a species of flowering plant in the genus Aconitum, of the family Ranunculaceae, native to Europe and northern Asia.
Lycoctonum is a rendering in modern Latin of the traditional name "wolf's bane". Wikipedia

Acrotriche.label: Acrotriche
Acrotriche.description:
Acrotriche is a genus of flowering plants in the family Ericaceae. Species occur in all states of Australia. They include
Acrotriche affinis DC. - Ridged Ground-berry
Acrotriche aggregata R.Br. Wikipedia

Adélie Penguin.label: Adélie Penguin
Adélie Penguin.description: The Adélie Penguin is a species of penguin common along the entire Antarctic coast, which is their only residence. Wikipedia

Adamawa Turtle Dove.label: Adamawa Turtle Dove
Adamawa Turtle Dove.description: The Adamawa Turtle Dove is a species of bird in the Columbidae family. It is found in Cameroon, Chad, Gambia, Nigeria, Senegal, and Togo. Wikipedia

Adonis aestivalis.label: Adonis aestivalis
Adonis aestivalis.description: Adonis aestivalis is a medicinal and ornamental plant. It is native to Europe but has been introduced elsewhere, such as the western and eastern parts of the United States. Wikipedia

Aegopodium podagraria.label: Ground Elder
Aegopodium podagraria.description: Aegopodium podagraria L. commonly called ground elder, herb gerard, bishop's weed, goutweed, and snow-in-the-mountain, is a perennial plant in the carrot family that grows in shady places. Wikipedia

Aerodramus.label: Aerodramus
Aerodramus.description: Aerodramus is a genus of small, dark, cave-nesting birds in the Collocaliini tribe of the swift family. Its members are confined to tropical and subtropical regions in southern Asia, Oceania and northeastern Australia. Wikipedia

Aeronautes.label: Aeronautes
Aeronautes.description:
Aeronautes is a genus of swifts in the Apodidae family.
It contains the following species
White-throated Swift
White-tipped Swift
Andean Swift Wikipedia

Aeschynomene.label: Aeschynomene
Aeschynomene.description: Aeschynomene is a genus of flowering plants in the family Fabaceae, and was recently assigned to the informal monophyletic Dalbergia clade of the Dalbergieae. They are known commonly as jointvetches. Wikipedia

Aesculus flava.label: Aesculus flava
Aesculus flava.description: Aesculus flava, the yellow buckeye, common buckeye, or sweet buckeye, is a species of deciduous tree. It is native to the Ohio Valley and Appalachian Mountains of the Eastern United States. Wikipedia

Aesculus pavia.label: Aesculus pavia
Aesculus pavia.description: Aesculus pavia, known as Red Buckeye or Firecracker Plant, is a species of deciduous flowering plant. Wikipedia

Aeshna isoceles.label: Aeshna isoceles
Aeshna isoceles.description: Aeshna isoceles is a small hawker dragonfly that is found in Europe, mostly around the Mediterranean, and the lowlands of North Africa. Its common name in English is Green-eyed Hawker. Wikipedia

Aethalops.label: Aethalops
Aethalops.description:
Aethalops is a genus of megabat in the Pteropodidae family. It contains the following species
Borneo Fruit Bat, Aethalops aequalis
Pygmy Fruit Bat, Aethalops alecto Wikipedia

Aethionema.label: Aethionema
Aethionema.description: Aethionema syn. Eunomia is a genus of flowering plants, within the family Brassicaceae, subfamily Brassicoideae. The genus is collectively known as the stonecresses. Wikipedia

Aetodactylus.label: Aetodactylus
Aetodactylus.description: Aetodactylus is a genus of ornithocheirid pterodactyloid pterosaur. It is known from a lower jaw discovered in Upper Cretaceous rocks of northeastern Texas, United States. Wikipedia

Africallagma cuneistigma.label: Africallagma cuneistigma
Africallagma cuneistigma.description: Africallagma cuneistigma is a species of damselfly in family Coenagrionidae. It is endemic to Zimbabwe. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist montane forests and rivers. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

African Collared Dove.label: African Collared Dove
African Collared Dove.description: The African Collared Dove is a small dove found in Africa in the arid region south of the Sahara. Its range extends in a band right across the continent, and into southern Arabia. Although it lives in arid lands, it is found around water sources. Wikipedia

African Crake.label: African Crake
African Crake.description: The African Crake is a bird in the rail family that breeds in most of sub-Saharan Africa away from the arid south and southwest. It is seasonally common in most of its range other than the rainforests and areas that have low annual rainfall. Wikipedia

African Hobby.label: African Hobby
African Hobby.description: The African Hobby is a small species of bird of prey in the Falconidae family. Wikipedia

African Olive Pigeon.label: African Olive Pigeon
African Olive Pigeon.description: The African Olive Pigeon or Rameron Pigeon is a pigeon which is a resident breeding bird in much of eastern and southern Africa from Ethiopia to the Cape. There are also populations in western Angola, southwestern Saudi Arabia and northern Yemen. Wikipedia

African Openbill.label: African Openbill
African Openbill.description: The African Openbill is a species of stork in the Ciconiidae family. Wikipedia

African Paradise Flycatcher.label: African Paradise Flycatcher
African Paradise Flycatcher.description:
The African Paradise Flycatcher is a medium-sized passerine bird.
The African Paradise Flycatcher is a common resident breeder in Africa south of the Sahara Desert. This species is usually found in open forests and savannah habitats. Wikipedia

African Pygmy Goose.label: African Pygmy Goose
African Pygmy Goose.description: The African Pygmy Goose is a perching duck from sub-Saharan Africa. It is the smallest of Africa's wildfowl, and one of the smallest in the world. Wikipedia

African Snipe.label: African Snipe
African Snipe.description: The African Snipe also known as the Ethiopian Snipe, is a small stocky wader. It breeds in eastern and southern Africa in wet mountain moorland and swamps at altitudes of 1,700–4,000 m. Wikipedia

African Wattled Lapwing.label: African Wattled Lapwing
African Wattled Lapwing.description: The African Wattled Lapwing or Senegal Wattled Plover is a large lapwing, a group of largish waders in the family Charadriidae. It is a resident breeder in most of sub-Saharan Africa outside the rainforests, although it has seasonal movements. Wikipedia

African bush squirrel.label: African bush squirrel
African bush squirrel.description: The African bush squirrels are a genus, Paraxerus, squirrels of the subfamily Xerinae. They are only found in Africa. Wikipedia

African softshell turtle.label: African softshell turtle
African softshell turtle.description: The African softshell turtle or Nile softshell turtle is a large species of turtle from fresh-water and brackish habitats in Africa and the Near East. Wikipedia

Agama (genus).label: Agama
Agama (genus).description: An agama is any one of the various small, long-tailed, insect-eating lizards of the genus Agama. The agamid genus is composed of at least 37 species across Africa, where they are the most common lizard. Wikipedia

Agelastes.label: Agelastes
Agelastes.description:
Agelastes is a small genus of birds in the guineafowl family. It comprises two species
White-breasted Guineafowl, Agelastes meleagrides
Black Guineafowl, Agelastes niger Wikipedia

Agile Frog.label: Agile frog
Agile Frog.description: The agile frog is a frog in the genus Rana in the family of the true frogs. Wikipedia

Agkistrodon contortrix.label: Agkistrodon contortrix
Agkistrodon contortrix.description: Agkistrodon contortrix is a species of venomous snake endemic to North America, a member of the Crotalinae subfamily. The common name for the species is the copperhead. Wikipedia

Aglia tau.label: Aglia tau
Aglia tau.description:
The Tau Emperor is a moth of the family Saturniidae. It is found in Europe.
The wingspan is 60–84 mm. The moth flies in one generation from March to July depending on the location. Wikipedia

Agnesiidae.label: Agnesiidae
Agnesiidae.description: Agnesiidae is a family of tunicates in the order Enterogona. Wikipedia

Agathis australis.label: Agathis australis
Agathis australis.description: Agathis australis, commonly known by its Māori name kauri, is a coniferous tree of Araucariaceae in the genus Agathis, found north of 38°S in the northern districts of New Zealand's North Island. Wikipedia

Agriades zullichi.label: Agriades zullichi
Agriades zullichi.description: Agriades zullichi is a species of butterfly in the Lycaenidae family. It is endemic to Spain. Wikipedia

Aglaonema.label: Aglaonema
Aglaonema.description: Aglaonema is a genus of flowering plants in the arum family, Araceae. They are native to tropical and subtropical regions of Asia. They are known commonly as Chinese evergreens. Wikipedia

Aglianico.label: Aglianico
Aglianico.description: Aglianico is a black grape grown in the Basilicata and Campania regions of Italy. The vine originated in Greece and was brought to the south of Italy by Greek settlers. The name may be a corruption of vitis hellenica, Latin for "Greek vine." Wikipedia

Afrocarpus.label: Afrocarpus
Afrocarpus.description: Afrocarpus is a genus of conifers belonging to the podocarp family Podocarpaceae. Afrocarpus was designated a genus in 1989, when several species formerly classified in Podocarpus and Nageia were reclassified. Two to six species are recognized. Wikipedia

Agyrtidae.label: Agyrtidae
Agyrtidae.description: Agyrtidae or primitive carrion beetles are a small family of polyphagan beetles They are found in mostly temperate areas of the northern hemisphere and in New Zealand. They are feeding on decaying organic material. Wikipedia

Agrostemma.label: Agrostemma
Agrostemma.description: Agrostemma is a genus of annual plants in the Caryophyllaceae family, containing the species known as corncockles. Its best-known member is A. githago, the Common Corncockle, which is a native of Europe where it is simply called "the Corncockle". Wikipedia

Agrostis stolonifera.label: Agrostis stolonifera
Agrostis stolonifera.description: Agrostis stolonifera is a perennial grass species in the Poaceae family. Wikipedia

Agrostis capillaris.label: Agrostis capillaris
Agrostis capillaris.description: Agrostis capillaris is a rhizomatous and stoloniferous perennial in the grass family. It is native to Eurasia and has been widely introduced in many parts of the world. Wikipedia

Aichryson.label: Aichryson
Aichryson.description:
Aichryson is a genus of about 15 species of succulent, subtropical plants, mostly native to the Canary Islands, with a few in the Azores, Madeira and Morocco, and one in Portugal.
The species of Aichryson are not frost-resistant. Wikipedia

Alcyonacea.label: Alcyonacea
Alcyonacea.description: The Alcyonacea, or soft corals, are an order of corals which do not produce calcium carbonate skeletons. Soft corals contain minute, spiny skeletal elements called sclerites, useful in species identification. Wikipedia

Ailanthus.label: Ailanthus
Ailanthus.description: Ailanthus is a genus of trees belonging to the family Simaroubaceae, in the order Sapindales. The genus is native from east Asia south to northern Australasia. Wikipedia

Albana (grape).label: Albana
Albana (grape).description:
Albana is a white Italian wine grape planted primarily in the Emilia-Romagna region.
The wine made from the grape, Albana di Romagna, was first awarded DOCG status in 1987. Wikipedia

Alexandrine Parakeet.label: Alexandrine Parakeet
Alexandrine Parakeet.description: The Alexandrine Parakeet or Alexandrian Parrot is a member of the psittaciformes order and of the Psittaculidae family. Wikipedia

Aldrovanda.label: Aldrovanda
Aldrovanda.description: Aldrovanda is a genus of carnivorous plants encompassing one extant species and numerous extinct taxa. Wikipedia

Akaniaceae.label: Akaniaceae
Akaniaceae.description: Akaniaceae is a family of flowering plants in the order Brassicales. It comprises two monotypic genera of trees, Akania and Bretschneidera native to southern East China, Vietnam, Taiwan, and eastern Australia. Wikipedia

Aleurites.label: Aleurites
Aleurites.description: Aleurites is a small arborescent genus of flowering plants in the tropical and subtropical regions of Asia, the Pacific and South America, belonging to the spurge family Euphorbiaceae. Wikipedia
